ive in that future, but I realized that I got the form factor wrong. A matt=
ress makes a lot more sense than a mirror.=C2=A0
When I asked David what Eight Sleep might be able to do in a decade, he rep=
lied, =E2=80=9CEvery night, you basically get a physical.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
That reminded me of the Ezra piece, so I asked him if they=E2=80=99d eventu=
ally be able to put MRIs inside of our beds, and he said that while it=E2=
=80=99s not possible in the current state =E2=80=93 a house=E2=80=99s floor=
s can=E2=80=99t support the weight of the magnets, wall outlets don=E2=80=
=99t have enough current, and you wouldn=E2=80=99t be able to wear metal je=
welry to bed =E2=80=93 =E2=80=9Ceverything is possible with the way that te=
chnology is progressing.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
The product that Eight Sleep is building and the way it=E2=80=99s built the=
