But we can end, like we began, with a thought exercise.=C2=A0
If a research team spun out of a top university today and told you that the=
y had dozens of sensors measuring hundreds of thousands of people for eight=
 hours a day, the ability to make adjustments and measure their impact, and=
 the ability to fund itself indefinitely, wouldn=E2=80=99t you think they h=
ad as good a shot as anybody?=C2=A0=C2=A0
Over the past decade, that=E2=80=99s the situation Eight Sleep has worked i=
tself into.=C2=A0
It built a consumer hardware product that a set of early adopters is raveno=
us about.=C2=A0
It maintained a high price point, which made acquiring customers harder in =
the beginning, but is paying off now that word of mouth has kicked in. The =
price point makes sense when you=E2=80=99ve heard from everyone from Lewis =
Hamilton to Peter Attia to Mark Zuckerberg to random people on social media=
 that it improves their sleep, and therefore their performance. $4,000 for =
years of improved performance seems like a bargain if it=E2=80=99s actually=
 true, and the more people you hear it from, the more you believe it.=C2=A0
Now, there are Eight Sleep Pods in hundreds of thousands of bedrooms across=
 the world, each packed with dozens of sensors learning, analyzing, and adj=
usting.=C2=A0
And Eight Sleep is cash flow positive, meaning that it controls its own des=
tiny, and will have a growing pile of cash to invest in research & developm=
ent and new products.=C2=A0
There=E2=80=99s some luck involved, too. With the insane pace of advancemen=
t in AI models=E2=80=99 capabilities, there=E2=80=99s never been a better t=
ime to be the company with the best data, and there might not be another co=
mpany building as comprehensive a data set on human bodies as Eight Sleep i=
s.=C2=A0
Certainly, Apple is on more wrists, and many users wear the watch most of t=
he day. That said, a watch can=E2=80=99t fit or power as many sensors as a =
mattress cover can, and it certainly can=E2=80=99t actively do anything to =
change your situation. It just measures. (Note: I wouldn=E2=80=99t be surpr=
ised if Apple tried to acquire Eight Sleep, but people say that about any s=
uccessful consumer hardware company.)
The HyperPod, when it arrives, will only enhance both what Eight Sleep can =
measure, what it can do to improve your sleep in a personalized way, and wh=
at it can learn.=C2=A0
Eight Sleep is in a surprisingly strong position, and its ability to achiev=
e the vision Matteo and Max first talked about at dinner in 2014 will come =
down to its ability to execute, to exogenous improvements in sensor technol=
ogy, and to the tractability of the problem. If better data really can lead=
 to better health =E2=80=93 a bet that a lot of companies have made and con=
tinue to make =E2=80=93 it seems that Eight Sleep has a prime seat at that =
table.=C2=A0
Better yet, it has moats. In When to Dig a Moat [ https://substack.com/redi=
rect/a70cf25c-dd00-4700-ab01-c9df6d12e6c2?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], I wrote that =E2=80=9CNew startups hav=
e a limited window of time during which they=E2=80=99re protected by the co=
ver of uncertainty to dig moats, and if they don=E2=80=99t dig them by the =
time others catch on, their excess profit will be competed away and they=E2=
=80=99ll struggle to achieve a good outcome.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
The idea that a mattress cover could lead to a predictive healthcare platfo=
rm was so outlandish that Eight Sleep has been able to build up advantages =
for a decade. To compete now, you=E2=80=99d need to build a consumer hardwa=
re company that sells mattress covers into hundreds of thousands of homes, =
something that maybe only Apple would have the scale and desire to do.=C2=
=A0
There are advantages to grinding it out.=C2=A0
I write these deep dives to learn about something that is endlessly fascina=
ting to me: the interaction between business models and technology, and the=
 application of both towards solving very big problems.=C2=A0
My big takeaway from studying Eight Sleep is this:=C2=A0
There are many paths to solving big problems, and the path you choose depen=
ds on the problem you=E2=80=99re trying to solve.=C2=A0
In some ways, it=E2=80=99s easier to build something really, really hard =
=E2=80=93 like a reusable rocket [ https://substack.com/redirect/ace998d2-f=
406-45bb-8422-6a86b32ad2c8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], autonomous weapons systems [ https://substack.com/red=
irect/11920c4b-63cb-4909-a38b-bde95c2b3e2b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], or advanced nuclear reactors [ https:=
//substack.com/redirect/fbcadf07-6553-4dee-a6c8-0906c130700a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOX=
AwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=93 knowing th=
at you will be able to sell to a small number of really big buyers like the=
 DoD or large businesses if you pull it off. And it almost seems more serio=
us, more pure to take that approach.=C2=A0
But for certain problems, selling to consumers is the only way to get what =
you need. Base Power Company [ https://substack.com/redirect/57ac015f-0a92-=
476f-912a-d50bb644e8e1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is a great example: its batteries need to be located next =
to homes to have the maximum impact on the grid. Eight Sleep is another one=
: there=E2=80=99s no way to get the data it needs or make the impact it wan=
ts than to do the hard work of convincing people to buy your product.=C2=A0
That approach may lead people to underestimate you. I underestimated Eight =
Sleep, even though I=E2=80=99ve slept on the Pod every night for the past c=
ouple of years. But looking at where Eight Sleep sits today, and how hard i=
t=E2=80=99s been to get to this point, I think it would be a mistake to und=
erestimate what they can do in the future.=C2=A0
Thanks to Dan and Claude for editing, and to Matteo, Alexandra, David, and =
Delian for your insights!=20
That=E2=80=99s all for today. We=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox with a We=
ekly Dose on Friday.=20
Thanks for reading,=20
Packy

