 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">Here&#8217;s a thought experiment.&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">If you wanted to build the world&#8217;s best predictive health platform=
, how would you do it? What attributes would it have?&#160;</p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;"><span>First, you&#8217;d need a lot of </span><strong>sensors</strong=
><span>. You&#8217;d want to track as much useful data about each person&#8=
217;s body as you could.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Second, yo=
u&#8217;d need </span><strong>adherence over a long period of time</strong>=
<span>. The best sensors are only as useful as each person&#8217;s willingn=
ess to use them, and data becomes more insight-rich over time.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Third, you&#8217;d want the ability to </span><=
strong>experiment</strong><span>. Tracking data is great, but using that da=
ta to adjust conditions and tracking the data that comes out of those adjus=
tments is better.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Finally, you&#821=
7;d want all of that across a </span><strong>large population</strong><span=
>. The more data you get from more people over time, the more accurate your=
 predictions get.&#160;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>That&#8217;=
s what </span><strong><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/e736143a-d21=
f-4078-82c9-36fc7a017cf0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: und=
erline;">Eight Sleep</a></strong><span> is building.&#160;</span></p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><span>It didn&#8217;t click for me for a long time. I&#8217;ve =
been sleeping on an Eight Sleep Pod for over two years. The company has spo=
nsored this newsletter. I had coffee with Eight Sleep&#8217;s co-founder, M=
atteo Franceschetti, in Miami as far back as 2021. I listened to him </span=
><em>say </em><span>that something like this was the goal on an old episode=
 of </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/379c9199-7500-4cc6-=
b668-fd8be7a32a25?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;=
">Invest Like the Best</a></em><span>. And certainly, I&#8217;ve seen all o=
f the tweets from Eight Sleep fanboys.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Bu=
t if I&#8217;m being honest, I thought all of it was really good marketing =
for what is ultimately just a really good mattress cover. I really do love =
my Eight Sleep Pod 4 Ultra. Sleeping cold even when Puja doesn&#8217;t let =
me turn the temperature down to the thinkboi-recommended 65&#176;F has been=
 a game changer. Getting a little elevation when I snore is a more recent g=
ame changer.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Sleep is great &#8211; I was =
converted from an investment banking hardo proud of my low sleep when I rea=
d Dr. Matthew Walker&#8217;s </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/f9cccbb2-e47a-4bb5-bf80-936a70aac82d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); te=
xt-decoration: underline;">Why We Sleep</a></em><span> &#8211; and Eight Sl=
eep helps me sleep better. So I&#8217;ve always bucketed Eight Sleep as a c=
ompany that uses technology to help people sleep better, which is great in =
its own right, because getting those eight hours makes the other sixteen so=
 much better.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But the full Eight Sleep pi=
cture clicked when I spoke with </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redi=
rect/441832f9-4ce7-44ef-b2e5-d13361eb3a03?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); tex=
t-decoration: underline;">David He</a><span>, Eight Sleep&#8217;s VP of Res=
earch &amp; Development.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>David is a=
 health monitoring lifer. He went from a University of Toronto undergrad in=
