217;s improving my sleep, but it&#8217;s also learning what works and what =
doesn&#8217;t for me, which is something that wrist-based wearables can&#82=
17;t do.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Eight Sleep&#8217;s products aren=
&#8217;t cheap. A Pod 4 Ultra starts at $4,049. But Matteo pointed out a be=
nefit to that price point: </span><strong>&#8220;At our price point, adding=
 another $10 sensor makes no difference; the margin doesn&#8217;t substanti=
